Html:
I want to use typed Forms inside an Access Addin. This allows access to controls with Intellisense and compile-time checks:<br />
<pre><code>NetOffice.AccessApi.Form frm1 = Main.App.Forms(&quot;Customers&quot;);

CustomersForm frm2 = new CustomersForm(frm1.UnderlyingObject);
string dummy2 = frm2.CustomerID.Value.ToString;

CustomersForm frm3 = new CustomersForm(frm1);
string dummy3 = frm3.CustomerID.Value.ToString;</code></pre>

I get it work passing &quot;Application.Forms&quot; collection in constructor:<br />
<pre><code>using NetOffice.AccessApi;

public class CustomersForm : NetOffice.AccessApi.Form
{

    public CustomersForm(NetOffice.AccessApi.Form frm)
    {
        base.New(Main.App.Forms, frm.UnderlyingObject);
    }

    public CustomersForm(object comProxy)
    {
        base.New(Main.App.Forms, comProxy);
    }

    public TextBox CustomerID {
        get { return (NetOffice.AccessApi.TextBox)this.Controls(&quot;CustomerID&quot;); }
    }

    public TextBox CustomerName {
        get { return (NetOffice.AccessApi.TextBox)this.Controls(&quot;CustomerName&quot;); }
    }

    public ComboBox CustomerCity {
        get { return (NetOffice.AccessApi.ComboBox)this.Controls(&quot;CustomerCity&quot;); }
    }

}</code></pre>

, where &quot;Main.App&quot; is &quot;Addin.Application&quot; property.<br />
<br />
I don't like to explicitly pass &quot;Application.Forms&quot; collection in constructor. But i didn't find how to use &quot;ParentObject&quot; argument of standard NetOffice.AccessApi.Form constructor.<br />
<br />
As said, it's working. But i'm wondering if there are a better way to do this. <br />
<br />
Any ideas?<br />
<br />
Thanks.<br />
